{
  "keyword": "RVKOBJAUT",
  "description": "Revoke Object Authority (RVKOBJAUT)",
  "parameters": [
    {
      "name": "OBJ",
      "description": "Object",
      "help": "Object (OBJ)\n\nSpecifies the objects to have specific authority revoked. If *ALL is specified for the object name, a library name must be specified.\n\nThis is a required parameter.\n\nQualifier 1: Object\n\nA generic name is a character string of one or more characters followed by an asterisk (*); for example ABC*. The asterisk substitutes for any valid characters. A generic name specifies all objects with names that begin with the generic prefix for which the user has authority. If an asterisk is not included with the generic (prefix) name, the system assumes it to be the complete object name.\n\nQualifier 2: Library\n\nUser libraries are all libraries with names that do not begin with the letter Q except for the following:\n\nAlthough the following libraries with names that begin with the letter Q are provided by IBM, they typically contain user data that changes frequently. Therefore, these libraries are also considered user libraries:",
      "inputType": "group",
      "required": true,
      "groupKind": "qualified",
      "children": [
        {
          "name": "LIB",
          "description": "Library",
          "help": "指定できる特殊値: *LIBL, *CURLIB, *ALL, *ALLUSR, *USRLIBL, *ALLAVL, *ALLUSRAVL",
